---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Red Team Kitchen — Cardinal & Code"
  description="Red Team Kitchen collects the public work of Alexios Bluff Mara LLC: Cortex, a Nous Research x Kimi brain-viewer project, and Mercury, a Gemma 4 Good local-agent experiment."
>
  <section class="hero wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Red Team Kitchen</p>
    <h1>Research demos, kept honest. <span class="cardinal">Code, artifacts, and the parts that still need a better architecture.</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Red Team Kitchen is the operating name of Alexios Bluff Mara LLC, a research-and-software
      lab in collaboration with Illinois State University. This site is being rebuilt as the
      stable public archive for our hackathon and research projects: what shipped, what did not,
      what can be replayed from the edge, and what still depends on the Seratonin RTX 5090 desktop
      being awake.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="cta primary" href="/cortex">Open Cortex</a>
      <a class="cta" href="/cortex">Cortex</a>
      <a class="cta" href="/mercury">Mercury</a>
      <a class="cta" href="https://github.com/AlexiosBluffMara">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-grid wrap">
    <article class="project-card">
      <p class="tag">Nous Research × Kimi Hackathon</p>
      <h2>Cortex</h2>
      <p>
        A browser brain viewer for TRIBE v2 predictions: submitted media becomes a 20,484-vertex
        cortical response, an ASCII brain-video artifact, and four narrations. The interactive app
        is working locally again on the 5090, but public live mode depends on that PC being online.
      </p>
      <a href="/cortex">View the Cortex page</a>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card">
      <p class="tag">Gemma 4 Good Hackathon</p>
      <h2>Mercury</h2>
      <p>
        A local-first agent experiment built from the Hermes codebase. The useful result is the
        evaluation and integration work; the current direction is to use Hermes directly instead of
        maintaining a separate long-lived fork.
      </p>
      <a href="/mercury">View the Mercury archive</a>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card">
      <p class="tag">Infrastructure</p>
      <h2>Cloudflare + Git</h2>
      <p>
        The healthy target is boring on purpose: Astro in Git, Cloudflare Pages for the site,
        R2 for durable media, and a clearly marked live Cortex tunnel only when the desktop is
        available.
      </p>
      <a href="/gemma">Read the Gemma notes</a>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: left;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--rtk-isu-gold);
    font-family: var(--rtk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-sm);
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-4);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 4.25rem);
    max-width: 20ch;
  }
  .cardinal { color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); }
  .lede {
    color: var(--rtk-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-md);
    margin: var(--rtk-sp-5) 0 var(--rtk-sp-7);
  }
  .lede strong { color: var(--rtk-text); }

  .cta-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--rtk-sp-3); }
  .cta {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-3) var(--rtk-sp-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-pill);
    color: var(--rtk-text);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-sm);
    transition: background var(--rtk-dur-short-2) var(--rtk-ease-standard),
                border-color var(--rtk-dur-short-2) var(--rtk-ease-standard);
  }
  .cta:hover { background: var(--rtk-surface-2); border-color: var(--rtk-text-muted); }
  .cta.primary {
    background: var(--rtk-cardinal);
    border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal);
    color: var(--rtk-text-on-cardinal);
  }
  .cta.primary:hover { background: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); }

  .project-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--rtk-sp-5);
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .project-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-sm);
    background: var(--rtk-surface-1);
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-5);
  }

  .project-card .tag {
    margin: 0 0 var(--rtk-sp-3);
    color: var(--rtk-isu-gold);
    font-family: var(--rtk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .project-card h2 { font-size: var(--rtk-fs-xl); }
  .project-card p { color: var(--rtk-text-muted); }
  .project-card a {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: var(--rtk-sp-2);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-sm);
  }
</style>
